.Title
[4mHISTOGRAM GENERATION Menu[0m                             (page 1 of 1)
.Proc FIT
fit      - Performs automatic linear stretches on halfword images,
           based on histogram. Can convert halfword to byte format.
.Proc HIST
[1mHIST[0m     - Prints DN-frequency histogram of all or portions of an 
           image along with image statistics.
.Proc HISTGEN
[1mHISTGEN[0m  - Generates histogram dataset of an image.
.Proc IDX
idx      - Displays VICAR images interactively.(Optional histograms)
.Proc MASKV
maskv    - Formats any image for film recording by placing an 
           information mask around the image. Labels and histograms optional.
.Proc MULTOVLY
multovly - IBIS program performing image overlay to produce a table 
           of DN-combination counts vs. DN-combinations (histogram of DN-
           combinations) in sorted order in an interface file.
.Proc SHIST
[1mSHIST[0m    - Produces a simple histogram on terminal screen.
.Proc VGRMASK
vgrmask  - Formats processd Voyager images into the Voyager 
           Systematic format with an information mask for film recorder
           display. (Optional histograms).
.help

The HISTOGRAM GENERATION section contains those programs which allow the 
user to generate a histogram of a dataset. These programs include:

fit                HIST               HISTGEN            idx
maskv              multovly           SHIST              vgrmask

.end
